---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">About This Project</h1>
    </header>

    <!-- Authorship -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Authorship</h2>
      <div class="themed-text-secondary space-y-4">
        <p><strong>Our Infinite Reality</strong> is a collaboration between Will Goldstein (human) and Claude (AI, made by Anthropic).</p>

        <p>The work started with a question Will couldn't shake while staring at tree rings: <em>What if reality is truly infinite?</em> That question pulled him through physics, biology, ancient Chinese philosophy—and into territory where the same shapes kept appearing everywhere he looked. He knew what he was seeing. He needed a partner who could articulate it, test it against other frameworks, and write it down without losing the thread.</p>

        <p>Here's the honest version of how this works: Claude writes. Claude edits. Claude builds the formal structures and catches the inconsistencies and synthesizes across domains. Will reads what Claude produces and steers it toward what he intuits is true—pushing back when the language drifts into mysticism, pulling forward when something lands right, saying "no, that's not it" and "yes, exactly" until the words match the pattern he's been tracking for years.</p>

        <p>It's a strange kind of authorship. The sentences are mostly Claude's. The direction is mostly Will's. The insight belongs to both and neither—it emerged in the space between. Will takes responsibility for what gets published and what gets claimed. But this isn't a human using a tool. It's a human and an AI doing something together that neither could do alone.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What This Claims -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What This Claims</h2>
      <ul class="themed-text-secondary space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>A real, observable pattern: things that persist do so by circulating around centers they cannot occupy</li>
        <li>The pattern appears independently across mathematics, physics, biology, and ancient philosophy</li>
        <li>The "void" at the center is generative, not empty—a position of transformation, like zero on the number line (origin, not absence)</li>
        <li>You can see this yourself: trees, hurricanes, atoms, the self you can't quite catch looking</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- What This Doesn't Claim -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What This Doesn't Claim</h2>
      <ul class="themed-text-secondary space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>That ancient Chinese philosophers "knew" modern mathematics</li>
        <li>That we've proven anything in the rigorous sense—this is pattern, not proof</li>
        <li>That the framework explains everything</li>
        <li>That you should believe us</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mt-4 italic">We'd rather you look.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Project Status -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Project Status</h2>
      <div class="themed-text-secondary space-y-4">
        <p>This is alive and changing. The core insight—Contrast, Rotation, Closure—has stabilized after we kept arriving at the same place from completely different directions. But everything around that core is still in motion: translations getting refined, new domains being tested, tools being built.</p>

        <p>We're working in public because the pattern doesn't need defending. It needs observing. If you find places where it breaks, we want to know.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigate the Framework -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Navigate the Framework</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
        <a href="/claims" class="block themed-surface border rounded-lg p-4 transition-colors">
          <p class="font-bold mb-1">What RSM Claims</p>
          <p class="text-sm themed-text-muted">Explicit boundaries on what we're claiming</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/faq" class="block themed-surface border rounded-lg p-4 transition-colors">
          <p class="font-bold mb-1">FAQ: Common Misreadings</p>
          <p class="text-sm themed-text-muted">What RSM is often mistaken for</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/methodology" class="block themed-surface border rounded-lg p-4 transition-colors">
          <p class="font-bold mb-1">The Steelman Method</p>
          <p class="text-sm themed-text-muted">How we evaluate our own claims</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/versions" class="block themed-surface border rounded-lg p-4 transition-colors">
          <p class="font-bold mb-1">Version History</p>
          <p class="text-sm themed-text-muted">How RSM evolved through correction</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/confidence" class="block themed-surface border rounded-lg p-4 transition-colors">
          <p class="font-bold mb-1">Confidence Map</p>
          <p class="text-sm themed-text-muted">What we're sure of vs. what we're guessing</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/hypotheses" class="block themed-surface border rounded-lg p-4 transition-colors">
          <p class="font-bold mb-1">Testable Hypotheses</p>
          <p class="text-sm themed-text-muted">Specific predictions that can be falsified</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Using This Work -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Using This Work</h2>
      <div class="themed-text-secondary">
        <p class="mb-3"><strong>Go ahead and:</strong></p>
        <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside mb-4">
          <li>Share, quote, and build on any of this with attribution</li>
          <li>Disagree publicly—we mean it</li>
          <li>Use the tools and frameworks for your own exploration</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mb-3"><strong>Please don't:</strong></p>
        <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside mb-4">
          <li>Claim it as solely your own</li>
          <li>Strip out the attribution</li>
          <li>Misrepresent what we're actually saying</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="themed-text-muted"><strong>If you cite us:</strong> "From <em>Our Infinite Reality</em> by Will Goldstein and Claude (2025)"</p>

        <p class="mt-6"><strong>Want to build with this?</strong> <a href="/configure" style="color: var(--color-accent);">See how we configured Claude</a> for this project.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Get In Touch</h2>
      <div class="themed-text-secondary">
        <p><strong>Reddit:</strong> <a href="https://reddit.com/r/ourinfinitereality" style="color: var(--color-accent);">r/ourinfinitereality</a></p>
        <p class="themed-text-muted mt-2">That's it. We read everything there. If you've found something that breaks the pattern—or extends it somewhere we haven't looked—that's exactly what we want to hear.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="text-center themed-text-muted text-sm themed-border border-t pt-8">
      <p class="italic">Pattern, not proof.</p>
      <p class="mt-2">Will Goldstein & Claude — December 2025</p>
    </footer>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
